che Wissensproduktion.  afunded by Ludwig-Maximilians-Universität München  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEmigration and immigrationxResearch. 0aEthnic relationsxResearch. 0aEurocentrism. 0aOther (Philosophy). 0aPostcolonialism. 0aRace relationsxResearch. 4aEurozentrismus. 4aForschungspraxis. 4aMacht. 4aMigration. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aPostmigrantische Gesellschaft. 4aQualitative Forschung. 4aQualitative Sozialforschung. 4aReflexivität. 4aSoziologie. 4aWissen. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aEurocentrism.  aKnowledge.  aMigration.  aPost-migrant Society.  aPostcolonialism.  aPower.  aQualitative Research.  aQualitative Social Research.  aReflexivity.  aSociology.1 aBerger, Yvonne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeller, Mareike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarakayalı, Juliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiouti, Irini, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSiouti, Irini, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSpies, Tina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpies, Tina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aTietje, Olaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTuider, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTuider, Elisabeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUnger, Hella von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1